headline: Agilent (NYSE:A) Reports Q4 CY2025 In Line With Expectations
summary: Life sciences tools company Agilent Technologies (NYSE:A) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 7% year on year to $1.8 billion. The company expects next quarter’s revenue to be around $1.81 billion, coming in 2.2% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.36 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Agilent: Fiscal Q1 Earnings Snapshot
summary: A) on Wednesday reported fiscal first-quarter net income of $305 million. On a per-share basis, the Santa Clara, California-based company said it had net income of $1.07. Earnings, adjusted for one-time gains and costs, were $1.36 per share.

headline: Agilent Reports First-Quarter Fiscal Year 2026 Financial Results
summary: SANTA CLARA, Calif., February 25, 2026--Agilent Technologies, Inc. (NYSE: A) today reported revenue of $1.80 billion for the first quarter ended Jan. 31, 2026, representing growth of 7.0% reported and up 4.4% core(1) compared with the first quarter of 2025.

headline: CeriBell, Inc. (CBLL) Reports Q4 Loss, Beats Revenue Estimates
summary: CeriBell, Inc. (CBLL) delivered earnings and revenue surprises of +16.76% and +4.40%, respectively, for the quarter ended December 2025. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?
